	// Dark Elves (Naggaroth)
	{
		"name": "Naggaroth",
		"leaderName": "Witch King Malekith",
		"adjective": ["Dark Elves"],
		"startBias": ["Tundra"],
		"style": "Elven",
		"outerColor": [105, 34,0]
		"innerColor": [0,0,0],
		
		"uniques": ["Starts with [Channeling]"],
		"cities": ["Naggarond","Ghrond","Karond Kar","Har Ganeth","Hag Graef","Clar Karond","","","",""],

		"civilopediaText": [
			{"text": "'We shall strike down our foes with sharp steel and cold hearts. The weak die so that the strong prevail and none shall be spared. Then and only then will our enemies know the true meaning of fear' - Malekith, Witch King of Naggaroth."},
			{"separator": true},
			{"text": "Those are the elves that were driven from the Ulthuan centuries ago, after a horrible civil war. Dark Elves, or Drucchi, as they are known in the Elven tongue, are close kin to High Elves, except for being paler, due to environment of their new, dark and cold home."},
			{"text": "Dark Elves, or Druchii as they call themselves, dwell in the realm of Naggaroth, the Land of Chill, far in the northern part of the New World. From their six menacing fortified cities, they march forth to enslave the free peoples of the Old World. The bulk of the Dark Elf army is made up of Spearmen & Warriors drawn from amongst the citizens of the Dark Elf cities. Sacrifices of blood are made in the name of Malekith the Witch King, and the bodies of slain victims litter the 9battlefields of their armies."},
